    "description": "Chemipro Kasei Kaisha, Ltd., together with its subsidiaries, manufactures and sells chemicals in Japan and internationally. It operates through Chemicals Business and Home Industry Business segments. The company offers plastic additives comprising ultraviolet absorbers, which include benzotriazole, benzophenone, triazine, and benzoxazinone; light stabilisers consisting of benzoate and HALS; and antioxidants, such as hindered phenol and thioether. It also provides organic electronic materials, color developers, and corrosion inhibitors; papermaking chemicals; and intermediates for dyestuff, pharmaceutical, and agricultural chemical products. In addition, the company offers plastic additives. Further, it develops, manufactures, and sells wood preservatives, fungicides, and insecticides. Chemipro Kasei Kaisha, Ltd. was incorporated in 1949 and is headquartered in Kobe, Japan."
